sentences: Manning currently teaches out of his vocal studio on Music Row in Nashville, Tennessee, along with his associate teachers Chanelle Guyton, Benny Meza, Ben Waites, and Claude McKnight.
In 2008 Manning was featured as a vocal coach and judge on CMT's television talent search, Can You Duet.
Manning also released a 16 song record titled Love Justice, under the band name 'Manning' in early 2015.
In 2016, Manning had his release party on an 800-acre historic farm in Franklin, with a follow-up performance at the Nashville venue "The Basement".
